<paragraph id="8BE98519D10D496F79C3C603FC6635D6" blockId="20.[188,1400,1832,2000]" lastBlockId="22.[188,1400,265,432]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="79" pageId="20" pageNumber="77">
BODY. BL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10D496D7825C604FE313300" box="[347,458,1867,1894]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.20 mm</quantity>
. Body smooth and shiny, sparsely pubescent, hairs very long. Head globular, slightly higher than long with hairs posteriorly (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10D496D7A2CC620FC3933EF" box="[850,962,1903,1929]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23 mm</quantity>
); eye oval, glabrous; maxillary palpi 5-segmented with one long seta on apical segment; antenna 11-segmented inserted on transverse shelf of low elevation; toruli separated by shallow cleft; scape as long as pedicel + F1–F5 combined, as long as head, with apical circumference slightly notched; pedicel as wide as scape, cylindrical; F1 narrower than pedicel and longer than wide; F2–F5 slightly shortening and widening; F6 two times as wide as long; F7–F9 wider than long, longer than previous flagellomeres, forming clava; F9 ovoid (antennomeres length of 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD10F496F7850C03DFE6335EA" box="[302,408,370,396]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">holotype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc-0.19; P-0.05; F1-0.03; F2-0.02; F3-0.02; F4-0.03; F5-0.03; F6-0.03; F7- 0.07; F8-0.07; F9-0.10); mandibles short, only crossing at tips.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF29D591D10C496C79C3C7BBFE793384" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468201" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6468201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468201/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" startId="21.[189,232,1780,1806]" targetBox="[271,1316,265,1743]" targetPageId="21">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10C496C79C3C7BBFE793384" blockId="21.[188,1399,1780,2019]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C79C3C7BBFED23368" bold="true" box="[189,297,1780,1806]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">Fig. 6. A</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10C496C7846C7BBFE173368" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[312,492,1780,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Basalys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villumi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7846C7BBFE173368" box="[312,492,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">Basalys villumi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D10C496C788BC7BAFDA93369" box="[501,594,1781,1807]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype (NHMD-608369), habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7DC3C7BAFB0F3369" bold="true" box="[1213,1268,1781,1807]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">B–D</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10C496C7C7DC7BBFEF53354" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baltica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7C7DC7BBFEF53354" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">Doliopria baltica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D10C496C7862C657FE7B3354" box="[284,384,1816,1842]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (NHMD-608374). 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7B95C657FD043354" bold="true" box="[747,767,1816,1842]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">B</emphasis>
. Habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7D38C658FBA03357" bold="true" box="[1094,1115,1815,1841]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">C</emphasis>
. Head in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C79C3C674FF293333" bold="true" box="[189,210,1851,1877]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">D</emphasis>
. Mesosoma and metasoma in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7B91C674FCD33333" bold="true" box="[751,808,1851,1877]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">E–H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10C496C7A42C674FBB23333" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[828,1097,1851,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Spilomicrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="succinalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7A42C674FBB23333" box="[828,1097,1851,1877]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">Spilomicrus succinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D10C496C7D28C673FB4E3330" box="[1110,1205,1852,1878]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7DBFC674FB0E3333" bold="true" box="[1217,1269,1851,1877]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">E–F</emphasis>
. Holotype (NHMD-607131). 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C78E4C611FE55331E" bold="true" box="[410,430,1886,1912]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">E</emphasis>
. Habitus in ventrolateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7A60C611FCCB331E" bold="true" box="[798,816,1886,1912]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">F</emphasis>
. Head and mesosoma in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7D94C611FAFA331E" bold="true" box="[1258,1281,1886,1912]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">G</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608344), habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10C496C7BAEC6CEFD1C33FD" bold="true" box="[720,743,1921,1947]" pageId="21" pageNumber="78">H</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608354), habitus in lateral view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; te = tergite excision. Scale bars: A, E–H = 1 mm; B = 0.5 mm; C–D = 0.25 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10F496F79C3C097FE59376D" blockId="22.[189,1401,471,779]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
MESOSOMA. Slightly shorter than metasoma (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7A58C098FC6F3594" box="[806,916,471,498]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
); pronotum with lateral posterior margin straight; mesoscutum large and slightly convex, without notauli or any other sulci; anterior scutellar pit deep, not divided, suboval; scutellum subquadrate; propodeum minutely punctuate in anterior part and carinate. Fore wing extending beyond metasoma (FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7A21C30EFC36363D" box="[863,973,577,603]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.77">0.77 mm</quantity>
), micropubescent and bordered with short setae; only Sc+R present, slightly separate from anterior margin of wing, distally ending in slight thickening of marginal vein. Hind wing length two thirds of length of fore wing (HwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7D85C3C8FA9136C4" box="[1275,1386,647,674]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
), micropubescent; with long setae along posterior margin and distal part of costal margin; three hamuli present; basal cell open. Legs slender, with only hind coxa and femur stouter; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10F496F79C3C27CFAA837D0" blockId="22.[186,1399,818,950]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
METASOMA. Petiole cylindrical, narrow, longer than wide (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7AE8C27DFC04372B" box="[918,1023,818,845]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7D28C27DFB3B372B" box="[1110,1216,818,845]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.06">0.06 mm</quantity>
), longitudinally striated, bearing several long hairs; gaster ellipsoidal (GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7AE5C219FBF23716" box="[923,1033,854,880]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.44">0.44 mm</quantity>
; GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD10F496F7D17C219FB223716" box="[1129,1241,854,880]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="0.21">0.21 mm</quantity>
), not sharply pointed at apex, smooth and glabrous; T2 and S2 longest; T2 covering at least two thirds of gaster, its anterior margin medially excised for distance subequal to petiole length; ovipositor slightly exerted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10F496F7994C292FED13791" blockId="22.[189,313,989,1050]" box="[234,298,989,1015]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7994C292FED13791" bold="true" box="[234,298,989,1015]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10F496F79C3C54FFEC2307C" blockId="22.[189,313,989,1050]" box="[189,313,1024,1050]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D10F496F79C3C50DFDCE3268" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10F496F79C3C50DFEBF303A" blockId="22.[189,324,1090,1116]" box="[189,324,1090,1116]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
<heading id="D0A13275D10F496F79C3C50DFEBF303A" bold="true" box="[189,324,1090,1116]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F79C3C50DFEBF303A" bold="true" box="[189,324,1090,1116]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D10F496F79C3C53EFDCE3268" blockId="22.[186,1399,1136,1550]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">
In 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F79A1C53EFDE230ED" author="Masner L. &amp; Garcia J. L." box="[223,537,1137,1163]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref15640" refString="Masner L. &amp; Garcia J. L. 2002. The genera of Diapriinae (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae) in the New World. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 268: 1 - 138. https: // doi. org / c 7 zvsh" type="journal article" year="2002">Masner &amp; García’s (2002)</bibRefCitation>
keys to the genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7A56C53FFC5C30EC" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1833" box="[808,935,1136,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Diapriinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7AC9C53FFB7E30EC" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[951,1157,1136,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baltica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7AC9C53FFB7E30EC" box="[951,1157,1136,1162]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Doliopria baltica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D10F496F7DF2C53EFB1230ED" box="[1164,1257,1137,1163]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out to 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F79C1C5DBFE2730C8" authority="Kieffer, 1910" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1910" box="[191,476,1172,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F79C1C5DBFEC830C8" box="[191,307,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Doliopria</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7845C5DBFE2730C8" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[315,476,1172,1198]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="46 - 48" refId="ref15145" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1910. Beschreibung neuer sudamerikanischer im Zoologischen Museum zu Berlin aufbewahrter Diapriiden. Entomologische Rundschau 1: 46 - 48. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 43669771 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: frons unarmed, antenna 11-segmented, notauli absent, wings fully developed, Sc+R separate from anterior margin of wing, basal vein absent. The description of the specimen is consistent with the original diagnosis of the genus by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7DE6C595FAB93092" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[1176,1346,1242,1268]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="46 - 48" refId="ref15145" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1910. Beschreibung neuer sudamerikanischer im Zoologischen Museum zu Berlin aufbewahrter Diapriiden. Entomologische Rundschau 1: 46 - 48. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 43669771 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer (1910)</bibRefCitation>
and the revised diagnosis of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F78ADC5B1FD093171" author="Masner L. &amp; Garcia J. L." box="[467,754,1277,1304]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref15640" refString="Masner L. &amp; Garcia J. L. 2002. The genera of Diapriinae (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae) in the New World. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 268: 1 - 138. https: // doi. org / c 7 zvsh" type="journal article" year="2002">Masner &amp; García (2002)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7B87C5B2FC3F3171" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[761,964,1277,1303]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baltica">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7B87C5B2FC3F3171" box="[761,964,1277,1303]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">Doliopria baltica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from extant representatives of this genus as follow: 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F78CDC46EFD1E315C" authority="Fouts, 1926" authorityName="Fouts" authorityYear="1926" box="[435,741,1312,1339]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F78CDC46EFDA8315C" box="[435,595,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. americana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7B25C46EFD1E315C" author="Fouts R. M." box="[603,741,1312,1339]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="167 - 179" refId="ref14614" refString="Fouts R. M. 1926. Notes on Serphoidea with descriptions of new species (Hymenoptera). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 28 (8): 167 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 24228" type="journal article" year="1926">Fouts, 1926</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has a two-segmented club (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7D59C46EFB4B315D" author="Fouts R. M." box="[1063,1200,1312,1339]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="167 - 179" refId="ref14614" refString="Fouts R. M. 1926. Notes on Serphoidea with descriptions of new species (Hymenoptera). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 28 (8): 167 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 24228" type="journal article" year="1926">Fouts 1926</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7DBDC46EFE963138" authority="Ogloblin, 1960" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1960" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyptera">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7DBDC46EFA8E315C" box="[1219,1397,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. brachyptera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F79C2C40BFE963138" author="Ogloblin A. A." box="[188,365,1348,1374]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref15770" refString="Ogloblin A. A. 1960. Tres especies nuevas del genero Doliopria del Ecuador (Diapriidae, Hymenoptera). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 22: 69 - 76." type="journal article" year="1960">Ogloblin, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has F9 more lengthened and is brachypterous; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7AF2C40BFB313138" authority="Ogloblin, 1960" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1960" box="[908,1226,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foersteri">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7AF2C40BFBEA3138" box="[908,1041,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. foersteri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7D67C40BFB313138" author="Ogloblin A. A." box="[1049,1226,1348,1374]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref15770" refString="Ogloblin A. A. 1960. Tres especies nuevas del genero Doliopria del Ecuador (Diapriidae, Hymenoptera). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 22: 69 - 76." type="journal article" year="1960">Ogloblin, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has short hairs on eyes, flagellomeres longer than wide and lacks the anterior scutellar pit; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7D37C427FF0131C2" authority="Ogloblin, 1960" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1960" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="equatoriana">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7D37C427FB0631E7" box="[1097,1277,1384,1409]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. equatoriana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7C79C428FF0131C2" author="Ogloblin A. A." pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="69 - 76" refId="ref15770" refString="Ogloblin A. A. 1960. Tres especies nuevas del genero Doliopria del Ecuador (Diapriidae, Hymenoptera). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 22: 69 - 76." type="journal article" year="1960">Ogloblin, 1960</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has F2–F5 longer than wide (Oglobin 1960); 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7A61C4C4FBB031C2" authority="Ferriere, 1929" authorityName="Ferriere" authorityYear="1929" box="[799,1099,1418,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collegii">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7A61C4C4FC6731C2" box="[799,924,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. collegii</emphasis>
Ferrière, 1929
</taxonomicName>
has F9 longer (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7C78C4C5FEBB31A1" author="Loiacono M. S. &amp; Margaria C. B. &amp; Aquino D. A." pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="320590" refId="ref15344" refString="Loiacono M. S., Margaria C. B. &amp; Aquino D. A. 2013. Diapriinae wasps (Hymenoptera: Diaprioidea: Diapriidae) associated with ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Argentina. Psyche 2013: 320590. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 2013 / 320590" type="journal article" year="2013">
Loiácono 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F79C3C4E1FF0A31A1" box="[189,241,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F7828C4E1FD8231A1" authority="Kieffer, 1910" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1910" box="[342,633,1453,1479]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F7828C4E1FE2E31A1" box="[342,469,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. flavipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F78A2C4E2FD8231A1" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[476,633,1453,1479]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="46 - 48" refId="ref15145" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1910. Beschreibung neuer sudamerikanischer im Zoologischen Museum zu Berlin aufbewahrter Diapriiden. Entomologische Rundschau 1: 46 - 48. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 43669771 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer, 1910</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has F5–6 as long as wide and the petiole shorter (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7DB5C4E2FA9231A1" author="Kieffer J. J." box="[1227,1385,1453,1479]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="46 - 48" refId="ref15145" refString="Kieffer J. J. 1910. Beschreibung neuer sudamerikanischer im Zoologischen Museum zu Berlin aufbewahrter Diapriiden. Entomologische Rundschau 1: 46 - 48. Available from https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 43669771 [accessed 2 Jan. 2021]." type="journal article" year="1910">Kieffer 1910</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD10F496F79C0C49EFDE3318D" authority="Kieffer, 1921" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1921" box="[190,536,1488,1515]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Doliopria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmecobia">
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F79C0C49EFE8F318C" box="[190,372,1488,1514]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">D. myrmecobia</emphasis>
Kieffer, 1921
</taxonomicName>
has a two-segmented club and the apical flagellomere sharply pointed at the apex (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D10F496F7851C4BBFDD23268" author="Loiacono M. S. &amp; Margaria C. B. &amp; Aquino D. A." box="[303,553,1524,1550]" pageId="22" pageNumber="79" pagination="320590" refId="ref15344" refString="Loiacono M. S., Margaria C. B. &amp; Aquino D. A. 2013. Diapriinae wasps (Hymenoptera: Diaprioidea: Diapriidae) associated with ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) in Argentina. Psyche 2013: 320590. https: // doi. org / 10.1155 / 2013 / 320590" type="journal article" year="2013">
Loiácono 
<emphasis id="B922590BD10F496F78D9C4BBFE213268" box="[423,474,1524,1550]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="79">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
